<topic id="editing-markup-text">
  <title>Editing XML Markup in Text Mode</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Author Editor<indexterm>edit markup</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> includes some useful actions that allow you to easily edit XML markup
      in <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode. These actions are available in the
        <uicontrol>Refactoring</uicontrol> submenu of the contextual menu<ph
        product="author developer editor"> and in the <menucascade>
          <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>Markup</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> menu</ph>, and many of the actions can also be done with simple keyboard
      shortcuts.</p>
    <section><title>Move Nodes</title>You can easily move XML nodes in the current document by using
      the following shortcut keys:<dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><shortcut conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/alt_up_shortcut"
              /></uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Moves the current node or selected nodes in front of the previous node.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><shortcut conkeyref="reusable_oxygen_shortcuts_list/alt_down_shortcut"
              /></uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Moves the current node or selected nodes after the subsequent node.</dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl></section>
